Soak the porcini mushrooms in 2 cups of warm water for Â½ hour beforehand.Chop onions and place in frypan with butter.Cook until onions are soft and golden.Add rice and toss for 3 minutes.Add one ladle of stock, stir constantly on medium flame, until the liquid is absorbed. Continue this process of adding 1 ladle of liquid and stirring for 10 minutes.Add nettles, stir cook for 5 minutes then add porcini and shiitake mushroom and soaking liquid.Cook until rice is al dente, approximately 18 minutes in total.Transfer to a plate and serve with grated parmesan.